SUMMARY:TOTAL CHAOS (USA) / RUMKICKS (KOR) (Uhrzeit prüfen)
LOCATION:Chelsea
DESCRIPTION:Doors: 20:00\, Start: 20:30   TOTAL CHAOS (Pomona / USA / Hardcore Punk) Total Chaos is an American hardcore punk band from Pomona\, California\, formed in 1989. Lead vocalist Rob Chaos is also co-owner of SOS Records with Ezzat Soliman\, owner of the Showcase Theater\, having released albums by classic punk and Oi! bands like the Exploited\, Vice Squad\, Sham 69\, Conflict\, the Adicts and Abrasive Wheels among others.[1] With help of Jay Lee from the band Resist and Exist\, the band started organizations such as United Valley Punks\, Orange County Peace Punks and Alternative Gathering Collective. Together\, they held such social events as Food Not Bombs\, helped open the Los Angeles Anarchist Center and supported the Big Mountain Indian Reservation. www.facebook.com/totalchaospunx/    RUMKICKS (Seoul / South Korea / Punk Rock) Rumkicks is a three-piece punk band based in Seoul\, South Korea\, that has been active since debuting in September 2018. In 2019\, two singles\, ’We’ and ‘Youth 18\,’ were released. In 2020\, we released our first ep ‘Brutality’. We followed up on our EP release in 2021\, with the single ‘Don’t Touch My Head\,’ which is about experiencing sexual harassment as an all-female band\, as well as the song about breaking the glass ceiling: ‘I don’t wanna die.’ It was our attempt to join the feminist movement. ‘Proud of madness\,’ the ‘Mad pride Seoul’ tribute song\, was released in 2022\, and we Participated in social movements to improve awareness of mental disorders. Later in 2022\, we came out with ‘Punk is Nowhere’ which hits back at all the hate comments we’ve received online calling us fake\, plastic\, and fashion punks. During the 2022 summer\, we successfully completed our first UK tour and performed at the legendary Rebellion Punk Festival. In early 2023\, we got the chance to do an Indonesian tour of 5 cities. 2023\, We released 1st full length ‘Born rude’ and did EU-UK tour 7 countries and 19 cities including Pod porou festival and Rebellion festival. And we went to Japan tour at September. amd we are going to play with The casualies ‘s European tour. And we are going to go to China tour at December. Through our music\, we want to deliver both joy and anger—a message to make the world a little better. www.facebook.com/rumkicks/?locale=de_DE    Tickets:  www.eventim-light.com/at/a/60fa5dffd95e696e2fb33355/e/6a392a6962a4c54f9f0f8313
URL:https://www.chelsea.co.at/concerts.php#concert_6713
